Locked architectural decisions

This schema reflects the Policy Resolution Model you've locked:

The client explicitly specifies:
name
version
schemaVersion
Parmana does not automatically discover or select a policy.
Parmana resolves the policy by matching the supplied name, version, and schemaVersion against the Policy Store.
If no matching policy exists, the request fails with POLICY_NOT_FOUND.
If the policy exists but the declared schemaVersion is incompatible, the request fails before policy evaluation (for example, with an INVALID_SCHEMA or equivalent validation error, as defined by your Error Model).
The resolved policy is recorded in the Execution Trust Record and is immutable for the lifetime of the Business Transaction.


{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://schemas.parmana.ai/common/policy.schema.json",
  "title": "Policy",
  "description": "Canonical Policy reference used for policy resolution.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "name",
    "version",
    "schemaVersion"
  ],
  "properties": {
    "name": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique policy name.",
      "minLength": 1,
      "maxLength": 255
    },
    "version": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Policy version.",
      "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+\\.\\d+$",
      "examples": [
        "1.0.0",
        "2.1.3"
      ]
    },
    "schemaVersion": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Signals schema version expected by the policy.",
      "pattern": "^\\d+\\.\\d+$",
      "examples": [
        "1.0",
        "2.0"
      ]
    }
  },
  "examples": [
    {
      "name": "payment-approval",
      "version": "2.1.0",
      "schemaVersion": "1.0"
    }
  ]
}